  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.13.4-stable\r\nGit Commit: 3f907d6a6f6de09cff1360ed529126765939851d\r\nCL client & version: prysm/beacon-chain:v4.0.8\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nOS version: linux ubuntu docker\r\nGo Version: go1.21.3\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nRunning below command\r\n```\r\ngeth --goerli --db.engine pebble --http --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --http.vhosts * --http.api eth,admin,txpool,debug,net,web3 --rpc.evmtimeout 1m --ws --ws.addr 0.0.0.0 --ws.origins * --ws.api eth,admin,txpool,debug,net,web3 --graphql --syncmode full --gcmode archive --cache 131072 --cache.preimages --datadir.ancient /root/.ethereum/ancient --maxpeers 128 --txlookuplimit 0 --metrics\r\n```\r\n\r\nGoerli archive node using pebble starts normally after upgrading to 1.13.4.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nGoerli archive node using pebble failed to start after upgrading to 1.13.4, The error is:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    2023-10-19T15:22:35.621008159Z 2023/10/19 15:22:35 Fatal: Failed to register the Ethereum service: MemTableSize (4.0GB) must be < 4.0GB\r\n```\r\nThe same command with same data starts successfully with 1.13.2\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n- A fully synced goerli archive node using pebble using 1.13.2\r\n- upgrade geth to 1.13.4\r\n- run `geth --goerli --db.engine pebble --http --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --http.vhosts * --http.api eth,admin,txpool,debug,net,web3 --rpc.evmtimeout 1m --ws --ws.addr 0.0.0.0 --ws.origins * --ws.api eth,admin,txpool,debug,net,web3 --graphql --syncmode full --gcmode archive --cache 131072 --cache.preimages --datadir.ancient /root/.ethereum/ancient --maxpeers 128 --txlookuplimit 0 --metrics`\r\n\r\n",
